oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Bethel College
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Exterior view of Bethel College and grounds. In 1842, the school was founded as Bethel Seminary and for five years was operated without a charter. The Seminary was founded and operated under the fostering care of the West Tennessee Synod of the Cumberland Presbyterian Church.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:source: Looking Back at Tennessee Photograph Collection, 1890-1981
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:subject: Universities & colleges
